abstract: Some traders questioned whether a recent upswing in the stock markets had raced too far ahead of the economy.
snippet: Some traders questioned whether a recent upswing in the stock markets had raced too far ahead of the economy.
lead_paragraph: A steep slide in the price of oil, copper and other commodities dragged Wall Street lower on Wednesday, as traders questioned whether a recent upswing in the stock markets had raced too far ahead of the real economy.

headline.main: Plunge in Oil and Copper Drags Wall Street Lower
